      "writtenOn": "2026-06-03T12:39:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hi Klement,\n\nDo you find ugly the way to generate/dump packets in netns or the way I configure linux-cp? Or both? :)\n\nI\u0027m also not happy with my approach but couldn\u0027t find any other ways to inject or dump packet in linux and not to introduce new dependencies.\n\nAlso, I want to underline that we want to configure things via linux:\n* enable lcp (I think can be hidden in VppInterface sub-class)\n* configuring IP address from linux\n* then LCP installs mcast routes\n* then we check both ingress and egress directions for mcast packets\n\nbut should all those linux handling go into VppInterface sub-class in your opinion?",
      "parentUuid": "48cadf63_06f0be16",
      "revId": "1641293b90cf818b9338684a45c79aaf523b8ab7",
